  "title": "Operations Crew",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Operations Crew Member (Funeral Services)</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>Highlights:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Career development opportunities — pathway to Funeral Director role</li>\n  <li>Open, friendly, and dynamic working environment</li>\n  <li>Attractive salary commensurate with experience and skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We are seeking a compassionate and reliable <strong>Operations Crew Member</strong> with a <strong>Class 3 or 4 driving license</strong> to join our dedicated team. This role plays a crucial part in supporting bereaved families and ensuring smooth, dignified funeral operations.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Offer comfort and assistance to bereaved families</li>\n  <li>Collect and transport the deceased with professionalism and care</li>\n  <li>Support family members throughout rites, rituals (all religions), and funeral processions</li>\n  <li>Present eulogies (all religions) to family members on the funeral day</li>\n  <li>Assist with ash collection and other related duties</li>\n  <li>Transport flowers, backdrops, and logistics for wake setup</li>\n  <li>Maintain the cleanliness and readiness of company vehicles, equipment, and facilities</li>\n  <li>Uphold service excellence and quality control standards</li>\n  <li>Project a positive and professional image at all times</li>\n  <li>Resolve operational challenges effectively</li>\n  <li>Perform other operational duties as assigned</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Possess a valid <strong>Class 3 and/or 4 Driving License </strong>as driving of hearse is required</li>\n  <li>Due to job nature, working during wee hours, weekends &amp; public holidays are required</li>\n  <li>Basic computer literacy</li>\n  <li>Capable of safely lifting, carrying, and handling coffins weighing from 80 kg.</li>\n  <li><strong>Conversant in Mandarin</strong> effectively as required during Chinese funeral rituals</li>\n</ul>",
